(95, 'Operating Systems', 'The primary purpose of an Operating System is:', 'Browse the internet', 'Manage hardware resources and provide a platform for applications to run', 'Scan for viruses', 'Configure network settings', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(96, 'Operating Systems', 'What does \"kernel\" refer to in an operating system?', 'A startup disk', 'The core component of the OS that manages CPU, memory, and device I/O', 'An antivirus module', 'A graphical user interface', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(97, 'Operating Systems', 'Windows Registry is:', 'A list of installed printers', 'A hierarchical database storing OS configuration, application settings, and user preferences', 'A disk partitioning tool', 'A type of file system', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(98, 'Operating Systems', 'NTFS offers which advantage over FAT32?', 'No advantages', 'Supports files larger than 4GB, file permissions, encryption, and journaling', 'FAT32 is faster', 'NTFS only works on external drives', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(99, 'Operating Systems', 'The Windows \"Safe Mode\" is used to:', 'Increase performance', 'Start Windows with minimal drivers to diagnose and repair startup issues', 'Increase security', 'Enable guest access', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(100, 'Operating Systems', 'In Linux, which command lists files and directories including hidden files?', 'dir /a', 'ls -la', 'show all', 'list -hidden', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(101, 'Operating Systems', 'The command \"chkdsk C: /f /r\" in Windows performs:', 'Formats C drive', 'Checks disk for errors (/f fixes them) and locates bad sectors (/r recovers data)', 'Defragments the drive', 'Clears temp files', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(102, 'Operating Systems', 'A process that is \"unresponsive\" in Windows can be terminated using:', 'Restart only', 'Task Manager → End Task, or taskkill command in CMD', 'Format the drive', 'Run virus scan', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
