(104, 'Operating Systems', 'The Windows Event Viewer is used for:', 'Playing media files', 'Viewing system, security, and application event logs for diagnostics', 'Configuring network', 'Managing printers', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(105, 'Operating Systems', 'In Linux, the command to change file permissions is:', 'attrib', 'chmod', 'chown', 'perm', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(106, 'Operating Systems', 'What does \"sudo\" mean in Linux?', 'Super User Desktop Operation', 'Execute a command with superuser (root) privileges', 'Shut down the OS', 'Switch default user', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(107, 'Operating Systems', 'Group Policy in Windows Active Directory environment allows IT administrators to:', 'Manually configure each PC', 'Centrally manage and enforce settings across all computers and users in the domain', 'Only change wallpaper', 'Only reset passwords', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(108, 'Operating Systems', 'The purpose of a \"swap partition\" in Linux is:', 'Store user documents', 'Act as virtual memory — overflow storage when physical RAM is full', 'Store OS updates', 'Boot the system', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(109, 'Operating Systems', 'Which Windows file system feature creates transaction logs to help recover from crashes?', 'FAT32 journaling', 'NTFS journaling', 'ReFS only', 'EXT4', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(110, 'Operating Systems', 'In a corporate bank environment, why is it critical to apply OS security patches promptly?', 'To improve screen resolution', 'To close known vulnerabilities that attackers exploit to compromise systems', 'To increase storage space', 'To add new features', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(111, 'Operating Systems', 'The Windows command \"sfc /scannow\" performs:', 'Formats the disk', 'Scans and repairs corrupted Windows system files', 'Displays IP settings', 'Lists running processes', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(112, 'Operating Systems', 'Remote Desktop Protocol (RDP) uses which default port?', '22', '80', '3389', '443', 2, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(113, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'What is malware?', 'Defective hardware', 'Any software intentionally designed to cause damage, steal data, or gain unauthorized access', 'A type of RAM', 'A network protocol', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(114, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'Phishing attacks are characterized by:', 'Physical theft of hardware', 'Deceptive emails or websites designed to trick users into revealing sensitive credentials', 'Overwhelming a server with traffic', 'Intercepting network packets', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(115, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'Ransomware is a type of malware that:', 'Slows down the computer', 'Encrypts victim files and demands payment for the decryption key', 'Steals passwords silently', 'Duplicates itself across networks', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(116, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'What does penetration testing involve?', 'Installing updates', 'Authorized simulated cyber-attacks on a system to identify security vulnerabilities before malicious actors do', 'Testing network speed', 'Scanning for viruses', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(117, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'The principle of \"least privilege\" means:', 'Give all users admin rights for efficiency', 'Grant users only the minimum access rights required to perform their job functions', 'Block all internet access', 'Share one admin account', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(118, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) adds security by:', 'Requiring two passwords', 'Requiring a second verification factor (e.g., OTP on phone) in addition to a password', 'Using a longer password', 'Encrypting only the password', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(119, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'A bank employee receives an email asking to urgently click a link and verify account credentials. This is MOST LIKELY:', 'A routine bank update', 'A phishing attack attempting to steal credentials', 'A software update notification', 'A scheduled system maintenance notice', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(120, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'SSL/TLS protocols are used to:', 'Speed up website loading', 'Encrypt data in transit between client and server (e.g., HTTPS)', 'Assign IP addresses', 'Scan email attachments', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(121, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'A DMZ (Demilitarized Zone) in network security is:', 'A geographic boundary', 'A network segment between the internal secure network and the internet, hosting public-facing servers', 'A type of firewall', 'A VPN configuration', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(122, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'Which of the following is the STRONGEST password?', 'password123', 'Admin2024', 'Tr@v3l!ng#2026$Bank', 'bankadmin', 2, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(123, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'An IDS (Intrusion Detection System) differs from an IPS in that:', 'They are identical', 'IDS only monitors and alerts; IPS actively blocks detected threats', 'IPS is older technology', 'IDS blocks traffic automatically', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(124, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'Social engineering in cybersecurity refers to:', 'Hacking via software exploits', 'Manipulating people psychologically to reveal confidential information or perform actions', 'Physical server attacks', 'Brute force password attacks', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(125, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'Full disk encryption on a bank laptop ensures:', 'Faster boot times', 'Data on the disk cannot be read without the encryption key, even if the drive is physically removed', 'Automatic backup', 'Remote access capability', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(126, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'How often should antivirus signatures be updated in a bank environment?', 'Once per year', 'Daily or automatically — new threats emerge continuously', 'Monthly only', 'Only when an infection is suspected', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(127, 'Cybersecurity & Security', 'A zero-day vulnerability is:', 'An old known vulnerability', 'A security flaw that is exploited before the vendor has released a patch', 'A vulnerability fixed immediately', 'A minor cosmetic bug', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(128, 'Software Testing', 'Alpha testing is performed by:', 'End customers publicly', 'Internal development and QA team before release', 'A third-party testing firm exclusively', 'Government auditors', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(129, 'Software Testing', 'Beta testing involves:', 'Internal team only', 'Selected external real-world users testing the product before general release', 'Load testing only', 'Only testing the UI', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(130, 'Software Testing', 'Load testing evaluates:', 'UI color schemes', 'System behavior under expected peak user load conditions', 'Code syntax errors', 'Database schema', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(131, 'Software Testing', 'Stress testing differs from load testing in that:', 'They are the same', 'Stress testing pushes the system beyond its designed limits to find the breaking point', 'Load testing is more extreme', 'Stress testing only tests memory', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(132, 'Software Testing', 'The correct order of software testing phases in a release cycle is:', 'Beta → Alpha → Production', 'Unit → Integration → System → UAT → Production', 'Production → Testing → Development', 'UAT → System → Unit', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(133, 'Software Testing', 'UAT stands for:', 'Universal Application Test', 'User Acceptance Testing — final testing by end-users to confirm the system meets requirements', 'Unit Automation Test', 'Unified API Testing', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(134, 'Software Testing', 'Regression testing ensures:', 'New features are added', 'Existing functionality still works correctly after code changes or updates', 'Performance benchmarks are met', 'Security patches are applied', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(135, 'Software Testing', 'A bank is deploying a new core banking system. Which testing type simulates hundreds of simultaneous transactions to check stability?', 'Unit testing', 'Load/performance testing', 'Syntax checking', 'Alpha testing only', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(136, 'Software Testing', 'The purpose of a test case is:', 'To write production code', 'A documented set of conditions and expected results used to determine if a software feature works correctly', 'To report bugs to management', 'To design the UI', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(137, 'Software Testing', 'Penetration testing in a bank environment specifically tests:', 'Network speed', 'Security defenses by simulating real attacks to find exploitable vulnerabilities', 'Printer functionality', 'Database backup integrity', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(138, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'Keystone correction on a projector is used to:', 'Adjust brightness', 'Correct trapezoidal image distortion caused by projecting at an angle', 'Change the resolution', 'Switch between input sources', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(139, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'A projector displays a trapezoid-shaped image instead of a rectangle. The MOST LIKELY cause is:', 'Bulb failure', 'The projector is not positioned perpendicular to the screen', 'HDMI cable fault', 'Incorrect resolution', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(140, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'Projector calibration involves:', 'Replacing the lamp', 'Adjusting brightness, contrast, color temperature, and geometry settings for optimal image quality', 'Changing the input source', 'Cleaning the lens only', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(141, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'Throw ratio of a projector defines:', 'Lamp wattage', 'The ratio of projection distance to image width — determines how far back to place the projector', 'Aspect ratio of display', 'Cooling fan speed', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(142, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'HDMI carries which types of signals?', 'Video only', 'Audio and video in a single cable', 'Audio only', 'Network data', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(143, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'A printer in the bank prints blank pages. After confirming there is ink/toner, the NEXT step is:', 'Replace the printer', 'Check if the cartridge has a protective tape still attached, re-seat cartridge, or run cleaning cycle', 'Format the PC', 'Reinstall Windows', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(144, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'A laser printer produces \"ghost images\" (faint duplicate of previous print). The MOST LIKELY component to replace is:', 'Drum unit/imaging drum', 'Paper tray', 'USB cable', 'Print head', 0, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(145, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'What does DPI stand for in printing?', 'Dots Per Interface', 'Dots Per Inch — measures print resolution', 'Digital Print Intensity', 'Data Print Interface', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(146, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'A printer shows \"Paper Jam\" but no paper is visible. What should a technician do?', 'Power off and replace the printer', 'Power off, open all access panels and carefully remove any paper fragments, clean rollers', 'Ignore the error and print again', 'Reinstall printer driver', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(147, 'Projectors & Peripherals', 'Which port/interface provides the fastest connection for a modern external hard disk?', 'USB 2.0', 'USB 3.1 Gen 2 / Thunderbolt 3', 'Parallel port', 'VGA', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(148, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'The 3-2-1 backup rule means:', '3 copies in 1 location', '3 copies of data, on 2 different media types, with 1 copy offsite', 'Backup 3 times per day', '3 users with backup access', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(149, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'An incremental backup:', 'Copies all data each time', 'Copies only data changed since the LAST backup (any type) — fastest to perform, slower to restore', 'Copies only data changed since last full backup', 'Deletes old backups automatically', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(150, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'A differential backup:', 'Copies all data', 'Copies only data changed since the LAST FULL backup', 'Copies files randomly', 'Backs up system files only', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(151, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'In a bank, the Recovery Point Objective (RPO) defines:', 'How fast a system recovers', 'The maximum acceptable amount of data loss measured in time', 'The cost of backup infrastructure', 'Number of backup copies required', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(152, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'Recovery Time Objective (RTO) refers to:', 'How much data can be lost', 'The maximum tolerable time to restore a system and resume operations after failure', 'Backup frequency', 'Storage capacity needed', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(153, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'Which backup medium is considered MOST reliable for long-term archival in banks?', 'USB flash drives', 'Magnetic tape cartridges or cloud with offsite redundancy', 'CD/DVD discs', 'Floppy disks', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(154, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'After a bank server hard disk fails, what is the FIRST action a technician should take?', 'Immediately replace the disk and reformat', 'Assess the RAID status and check if data is still accessible before making changes', 'Call the server vendor only', 'Shut down all banking services permanently', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(155, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'RAID 1 can be considered a form of:', 'Data performance optimization', 'Continuous real-time backup/redundancy (mirroring)', 'Archival backup', 'Offsite backup', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(156, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'Cloud backup in a bank environment offers which advantage?', 'Free unlimited storage', 'Offsite data protection accessible from anywhere with internet connectivity', 'Faster than local backup always', 'No encryption needed', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(157, 'Data Backup & Recovery', 'When recovering from a ransomware attack, the BEST recovery approach is:', 'Pay the ransom immediately', 'Isolate infected systems, wipe and restore from clean pre-infection backup, investigate entry point', 'Restart the server', 'Run antivirus only', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(158, 'Software Installation', 'Before installing any new application on a bank workstation, a technician should FIRST:', 'Install immediately to save time', 'Verify the software is on the approved software list and obtain proper authorization', 'Download from any website', 'Disable antivirus permanently', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(159, 'Software Installation', 'A software installation fails with \"Insufficient disk space\". The FIRST corrective action is:', 'Buy a new computer', 'Free up disk space using Disk Cleanup, remove unused applications, or move files', 'Reinstall the OS', 'Upgrade RAM', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(160, 'Software Installation', 'Which of the following is a valid reason to use a virtual machine (VM) in a bank?', 'Virtual machines are slower', 'Testing software in isolated environments without affecting the production system', 'VMs cannot connect to networks', 'VMs replace physical servers always', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(161, 'Software Installation', 'License compliance in a corporate bank means:', 'Installing as many copies as needed', 'Ensuring the number of software installations does not exceed the purchased license count', 'Using only free software', 'Sharing one license across all PCs', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(162, 'Software Installation', 'After installing a new application, a user reports their computer is slower. What should be investigated?', 'Replace RAM immediately', 'Check if the application runs background processes or services consuming CPU/RAM via Task Manager', 'Replace the hard disk', 'Reinstall Windows', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(163, 'Software Installation', 'A technician is installing a network printer for multiple users. The correct approach on a Windows domain is:', 'Install printer on each PC individually', 'Deploy the printer via Group Policy so it is automatically installed on all relevant domain computers', 'Email driver files to each user', 'Use USB cable for all users', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(164, 'Software Installation', 'Operating system updates in a bank environment should be:', 'Never applied', 'Applied immediately the moment available on all machines', 'Tested in a controlled environment first then deployed after approval', 'Applied only to servers', 2, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(165, 'Software Installation', 'What is the purpose of a \"staging environment\" in IT?', 'For storing backups', 'A replica of the production environment used for testing changes before they go live', 'A meeting room for IT staff', 'A backup server only', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(166, 'Software Installation', 'Which of the following is the SAFEST source to download software for a bank workstation?', 'Any website with a \"Download\" button', 'Vendor\'s official website or organization\'s internal software repository', 'Third-party download aggregators', 'Torrent sites for speed', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(167, 'Software Installation', 'Unattended/silent installation of software means:', 'Software installs with errors', 'Software installs automatically without user interaction — useful for mass deployment', 'Installation takes longer', 'Software requires special hardware', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(168, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'In a banking environment, ICT system \"uptime\" refers to:', 'Time employees work', 'The percentage of time IT systems are operational and available — critical for 24/7 banking services', 'Power consumption', 'Storage availability', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(169, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'Why is a UPS (Uninterruptible Power Supply) critical in a bank data center?', 'For cooling purposes', 'Provides immediate battery backup during power outages preventing data loss and allowing graceful shutdown', 'To boost internet speed', 'To cool servers', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(170, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'Active Directory in a bank is used to:', 'Browse the internet', 'Centrally manage user accounts, authentication, security policies, and access to network resources', 'Store financial transaction logs', 'Manage backup tapes', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(171, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'A bank ICT technician must document all IT incidents because:', 'It is just a formality', 'Documentation creates an audit trail, helps identify recurring problems, and supports compliance requirements', 'Managers require it for pay', 'Documents replace backups', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(172, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'What is a \"change management\" process in IT?', 'Changing user passwords regularly', 'A formal process to review, approve, and implement IT changes to minimize risk to operations', 'Replacing hardware quarterly', 'Updating antivirus definitions', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(173, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'ITIL (Information Technology Infrastructure Library) is:', 'A software application', 'A framework of best practices for IT service management used by organizations including banks', 'A hardware standard', 'A type of firewall', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(174, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'A Service Level Agreement (SLA) in an IT context defines:', 'Employee work hours', 'Agreed levels of service quality, availability, and response/resolution times between IT and business units', 'Hardware specifications', 'Network topology', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(175, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'An IT technician at a bank must escalate a network issue that has been unresolved for over 2 hours. Escalation means:', 'Giving up on the issue', 'Passing the issue to a higher-level technician or specialist who has more expertise or authority to resolve it', 'Reporting to police', 'Restarting all servers', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(176, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'Core Banking System (CBS) downtime impacts:', 'Only IT department', 'All banking transactions including deposits, withdrawals, transfers and customer services', 'Only internet banking', 'Only ATMs', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(177, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'When a bank employee reports that they cannot access their email, the technician should FIRST:', 'Reinstall Windows', 'Verify network connectivity, check if the mail server is running, and test with another account', 'Replace the computer', 'Call the email vendor', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(178, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'Data classification in a bank means:', 'Organizing physical files', 'Categorizing data (Public, Internal, Confidential, Restricted) to apply appropriate security controls', 'Filing documents alphabetically', 'Labeling hardware', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(179, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'An ICT technician notices an unusual spike in network traffic at 2 AM. This could indicate:', 'Routine backup operations (if scheduled) or a potential security incident requiring investigation', 'Normal behavior always', 'Network cables loosening', 'UPS switching to battery', 0, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(180, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'Which of the following is the CORRECT way to handle a decommissioned bank laptop?', 'Give to any employee as a gift', 'Follow the asset disposal policy — data sanitization, formal asset write-off, and environmentally responsible disposal', 'Throw in regular trash', 'Format quickly and sell', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(181, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'IT asset management in a bank involves:', 'Only tracking computers', 'Tracking all hardware and software assets including procurement, deployment, maintenance, and disposal lifecycle', 'Only tracking licenses', 'Only counting servers', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(182, 'Bank ICT Operations', 'A bank has scheduled maintenance on Saturday night. What must the IT team prepare before starting?', 'Nothing — just begin', 'A rollback plan in case changes cause issues, backups of current state, and stakeholder notifications', 'Only inform the manager verbally', 'Only update documentation after', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(183, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'A hypervisor is:', 'A high-performance CPU', 'Software that creates and manages virtual machines on physical hardware', 'A type of network switch', 'A cloud storage service', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(184, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'Type 1 hypervisor (bare-metal) differs from Type 2 in that:', 'Type 2 is faster', 'Type 1 runs directly on hardware without a host OS (e.g., VMware ESXi), making it more efficient', 'Type 1 requires a host OS', 'They are identical', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(185, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'The primary benefit of server virtualization in a bank is:', 'Reduces electricity to zero', 'Multiple virtual servers on one physical host — better hardware utilization and reduced costs', 'Eliminates need for IT staff', 'Automatic data backup', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(186, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'Cloud computing \"IaaS\" provides:', 'Software applications over internet', 'Infrastructure (virtual servers, storage, networking) as a service — customer manages OS upward', 'Only email services', 'Physical servers at client site', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(187, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'SaaS (Software as a Service) means:', 'In-house installed software', 'Software hosted and delivered over the internet — users access via browser (e.g., Microsoft 365)', 'Server hardware rental', 'Storage-as-a-service', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(188, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'A snapshot in virtualization allows:', 'Taking a photo of the screen', 'Capturing the exact state of a VM at a point in time for quick rollback if changes cause issues', 'Backing up physical servers', 'Creating user accounts', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 16:25:36');
INSERT INTO `questions` (`id`, `category`, `question`, `option_a`, `option_b`, `option_c`, `option_d`, `correct_answer`, `difficulty`, `created_at`) VALUES
(189, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'In a private cloud model, infrastructure is:', 'Shared with the public', 'Owned and operated for a single organization — greater control and security, suitable for banks', 'Free of charge', 'Managed entirely by a third party with no control', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(190, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'Live migration of virtual machines refers to:', 'Copying VM files to USB', 'Moving a running VM from one physical host to another with minimal or no downtime', 'Migrating user data', 'Backing up the VM', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(191, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'Which cloud service model gives the MOST control over the environment to the customer?', 'SaaS', 'IaaS', 'PaaS', 'DaaS', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(192, 'Virtualization & Cloud', 'Containerization (e.g., Docker) differs from full virtualization in that:', 'Containers are slower', 'Containers share the host OS kernel making them lightweight and faster to start than full VMs', 'Containers require more RAM', 'Containers have their own OS', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 16:25:36'),
(193, 'Software Installation', 'What is the FIRST step before installing any new operating system on a bank computer?', 'Insert the installation media immediately', 'Back up all user data and verify the backup is readable', 'Format the hard drive', 'Disable the antivirus software', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(194, 'Software Installation', 'A technician receives an error \"This app has been blocked by your system administrator\" when installing software. This is MOST likely due to:', 'Corrupted installation file', 'Group Policy or User Account Control restrictions', 'Insufficient RAM', 'Outdated graphics driver', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(195, 'Software Installation', 'What does \"clean install\" of an operating system mean?', 'Installing over an existing OS without deleting files', 'Wiping the drive completely and installing fresh OS', 'Using a cleaning disk first', 'Installing only security updates', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(196, 'Software Installation', 'Which tool in Windows allows you to create a bootable USB drive from an ISO file?', 'Disk Cleanup', 'Rufus or Windows Media Creation Tool', 'Device Manager', 'Registry Editor', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(197, 'Software Installation', 'A user reports that after installing a new application, their computer crashes frequently. What is the BEST troubleshooting step?', 'Ignore the issue', 'Boot into Safe Mode and uninstall the recently added application', 'Replace the hard drive', 'Update the BIOS', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(198, 'Software Installation', 'What is the purpose of a \"checksum\" or \"hash\" when downloading software?', 'To speed up the download', 'To verify the file integrity and authenticity after download', 'To reduce file size', 'To automatically install the software', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(199, 'Software Installation', 'Which Windows feature allows you to roll back a device driver to a previous version?', 'System Restore', 'Device Manager → Driver → Roll Back Driver', 'Control Panel → Programs', 'Command Prompt → sfc /scannow', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(200, 'Software Installation', 'When deploying software to multiple computers in a bank, what is the MOST efficient method?', 'Visit each computer individually', 'Use centralized deployment tools like PDQ Deploy or SCCM', 'Email the installer to all users', 'Copy the installer to a shared folder and let users run it', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(201, 'Software Installation', 'A technician is installing software that requires a license key. Where should this key be stored securely?', 'On a sticky note attached to the monitor', 'In a password-protected asset management system or secure documentation repository', 'In a text file on the desktop', 'Shared via email to all staff', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(202, 'Software Installation', 'What does \"dependency\" mean in software installation?', 'The software depends on the user to click next', 'Additional software or libraries required for the main software to function', 'A type of license agreement', 'The installation time required', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(203, 'Maintenance', 'How often should preventive maintenance be performed on bank workstations?', 'Only when something breaks', 'On a regular schedule (e.g., monthly or quarterly) based on bank policy', 'Once per year', 'Never, modern computers don\'t need maintenance', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(204, 'Maintenance', 'What is the safest way to clean dust from inside a computer case?', 'Use a vacuum cleaner', 'Use compressed air while holding fans to prevent spinning', 'Use a wet cloth', 'Blow with mouth', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(205, 'Maintenance', 'Why should you hold fan blades in place when using compressed air?', 'To make the fan spin faster', 'To prevent overspinning which can damage fan bearings or generate back EMF', 'To clean better', 'To reduce noise', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(206, 'Maintenance', 'What is thermal paste and when should it be reapplied?', 'A cleaning solution for screens', 'A compound that transfers heat from CPU to heatsink; reapply every few years or when overheating occurs', 'A type of adhesive for RAM', 'A lubricant for fans', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(207, 'Maintenance', 'Which Windows built-in tool removes temporary files and system cache?', 'Disk Cleanup (cleanmgr)', 'Defragment and Optimize Drives', 'Performance Monitor', 'Event Viewer', 0, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(208, 'Maintenance', 'A laptop battery drains very quickly. What maintenance action might help?', 'Replace the hard drive', 'Calibrate the battery and check for power-hungry background apps', 'Install more RAM', 'Update the sound driver', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
