(313, 'Peripherals Continued', 'What is the difference between inkjet and laser printers?', 'No difference', 'Inkjet uses liquid ink, good for photos; laser uses toner powder, faster for text', 'Laser is older', 'Inkjet is faster', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(314, 'Peripherals Continued', 'A laser printer prints vertical black lines. What is the MOST likely cause?', 'Low toner', 'A scratched or damaged drum unit', 'Empty paper tray', 'Faulty USB cable', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(315, 'Peripherals Continued', 'What is \"duplex printing\"?', 'Printing on both sides of the paper automatically', 'Printing two copies', 'Printing in color', 'Printing multiple pages per sheet', 0, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(316, 'Peripherals Continued', 'A projector image is blurry. What should be adjusted FIRST?', 'The resolution', 'The focus ring on the projector lens', 'The brightness setting', 'The keystone correction', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(317, 'Peripherals Continued', 'What is \"keystone correction\" on a projector?', 'Changing the lamp', 'Digitally correcting trapezoidal distortion caused by angled projection', 'Adjusting color', 'Changing input source', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(318, 'Peripherals Continued', 'A headset microphone is not working. What is a common first check?', 'Replace the headset', 'Check if the microphone is muted or not selected as input device in OS sound settings', 'Reinstall Windows', 'Replace the sound card', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(319, 'Peripherals Continued', 'What is a KVM switch?', 'A type of keyboard', 'A device that allows one keyboard, mouse, and monitor to control multiple computers', 'A network switch', 'A power supply', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
