(321, 'Network Advanced', 'What is VLAN?', 'Virtual Local Area Network — logically segments a physical network', 'Very Large Area Network', 'Virtual Link Access Node', 'Voice LAN', 0, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(322, 'Network Advanced', 'What is the purpose of a VPN in a bank?', 'To speed up internet', 'To create an encrypted tunnel for secure remote access to the bank network', 'To block websites', 'To assign IP addresses', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(323, 'Network Advanced', 'What is DNS?', 'Domain Name System — translates domain names to IP addresses', 'Digital Network Service', 'Data Node Server', 'Dynamic Name Service', 0, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(324, 'Network Advanced', 'What port does DNS typically use?', '53', '80', '443', '25', 0, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(325, 'Network Advanced', 'What is DHCP?', 'Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol — automatically assigns IP addresses', 'Digital Hardware Control Protocol', 'Domain Host Control Protocol', 'Data Handling Program', 0, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(326, 'Network Advanced', 'What is the purpose of subnetting?', 'To slow down the network', 'To divide a network into smaller, more manageable segments and reduce broadcast traffic', 'To increase internet speed', 'To assign MAC addresses', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(327, 'Network Advanced', 'What is a MAC address?', 'A type of computer', 'A unique hardware identifier assigned to network interfaces', 'An IP address', 'A password', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(328, 'Network Advanced', 'How many bits are in an IPv4 address?', '32 bits', '64 bits', '128 bits', '16 bits', 0, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(329, 'Network Advanced', 'How many bits are in an IPv6 address?', '32 bits', '64 bits', '128 bits', '256 bits', 2, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(330, 'Network Advanced', 'What is the loopback address for IPv4?', '0.0.0.0', '255.255.255.255', '127.0.0.1', '192.168.1.1', 2, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(331, 'Network Advanced', 'What is a firewall rule?', 'A type of cable', 'A configured policy that allows or denies traffic based on criteria like IP, port, protocol', 'A backup setting', 'A user account', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(332, 'Network Advanced', 'What is the difference between TCP and UDP?', 'No difference', 'TCP is connection-oriented (reliable); UDP is connectionless (faster, no guarantee)', 'UDP is more reliable', 'TCP is faster', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(333, 'Network Advanced', 'What port does HTTP use?', '80', '443', '8080', '21', 0, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(334, 'Network Advanced', 'What port does HTTPS use?', '80', '443', '8080', '22', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(335, 'Network Advanced', 'What is the purpose of a proxy server?', 'To store files', 'To act as an intermediary between clients and servers, often for security or caching', 'To assign IP addresses', 'To route switches', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(336, 'Security Advanced', 'What is ransomware?', 'Software that speeds up the computer', 'Malware that encrypts files and demands payment for decryption', 'A type of antivirus', 'A network protocol', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(337, 'Security Advanced', 'What is a DDoS attack?', 'Distributed Denial of Service — overwhelming a server with traffic to make it unavailable', 'Direct Data Output System', 'Digital Denial of Security', 'Data Distribution Service', 0, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(338, 'Security Advanced', 'What is the purpose of penetration testing?', 'To test network speed', 'Authorized simulated attacks to identify vulnerabilities before real attackers do', 'To install software', 'To back up data', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(339, 'Security Advanced', 'What is encryption?', 'Making data larger', 'Converting data into a coded format that requires a key to decode', 'Deleting data', 'Copying data', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(340, 'Security Advanced', 'What is the difference between symmetric and asymmetric encryption?', 'No difference', 'Symmetric uses one key; asymmetric uses a key pair (public/private)', 'Asymmetric is faster', 'Symmetric is more secure', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(341, 'Security Advanced', 'What is a certificate authority (CA)?', 'A government agency', 'A trusted entity that issues digital certificates for secure communications', 'A type of antivirus', 'A network router', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(342, 'Security Advanced', 'What is a brute force attack?', 'Using physical force on a computer', 'Repeatedly trying many passwords until the correct one is found', 'A type of virus', 'A network failure', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(343, 'Security Advanced', 'What is a honeypot in cybersecurity?', 'A sweet treat', 'A decoy system designed to attract and trap attackers', 'A type of firewall', 'A backup server', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(344, 'Security Advanced', 'What is the purpose of security awareness training for bank employees?', 'To fill time', 'To educate users about threats like phishing and social engineering to reduce human error', 'To sell products', 'To test network speed', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(345, 'Security Advanced', 'What is a \"shoulder surfing\" attack?', 'Surfing the internet', 'Watching someone enter their password over their shoulder', 'A type of malware', 'A network attack', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(346, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'What is the purpose of defragmentation on an HDD?', 'To delete files', 'To reorganize fragmented data for faster access', 'To encrypt the drive', 'To compress files', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(347, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'Why should you NOT defragment an SSD?', 'It is impossible', 'It causes unnecessary write cycles and reduces SSD lifespan with no performance benefit', 'SSDs do not need it but it is safe', 'It makes SSDs faster', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(348, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'What is \"TRIM\" command for SSDs?', 'A command to delete files', 'A command that helps the SSD manage unused blocks and maintain performance', 'A backup command', 'A network command', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(349, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'How often should a bank\'s server room air filters be checked?', 'Once per year', 'Monthly or quarterly depending on environment', 'Never', 'Only when server overheats', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(350, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'What is the ideal temperature range for a server room?', '50-60°F (10-15°C)', '68-72°F (20-22°C) typically recommended', '80-90°F (27-32°C)', 'Below freezing', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(351, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'What is humidity control important in a server room?', 'For employee comfort', 'Too low humidity causes static discharge; too high causes condensation and corrosion', 'To save electricity', 'To reduce noise', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(352, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'What is the first sign of a failing hard drive often reported by S.M.A.R.T.?', 'Computer turns off', 'Clicking sounds or S.M.A.R.T. warnings in system logs', 'Screen flickering', 'Keyboard not working', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(353, 'Maintenance Advanced', 'What is \"burn-in testing\" for new hardware?', 'Testing with fire', 'Running intensive tests on new components to ensure stability before deployment', 'A type of soldering', 'Cleaning hardware', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(354, 'Disaster Recovery', 'What is a disaster recovery plan (DRP)?', 'A plan for daily work', 'A documented process to recover IT infrastructure after a major disaster like fire, flood, or cyberattack', 'A backup schedule', 'A network diagram', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(355, 'Disaster Recovery', 'What is the difference between a backup and a disaster recovery plan?', 'No difference', 'Backup is data copies; DRP includes procedures, people, and infrastructure to restore operations', 'DRP is only for data', 'Backup is more important', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(356, 'Disaster Recovery', 'What is a \"warm site\" in disaster recovery?', 'A heated building', 'A partially equipped backup site that can be made operational within hours', 'A fully equipped site ready immediately', 'A site with no equipment', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(357, 'Disaster Recovery', 'What is a \"cold site\"?', 'A refrigerated room', 'A backup site with basic infrastructure but no equipment, requiring days or weeks to become operational', 'A site with full equipment', 'A cloud backup', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(358, 'Disaster Recovery', 'What is a \"hot site\"?', 'A site with high temperature', 'A fully equipped, ready-to-operate backup site with real-time data replication', 'A site under construction', 'A storage closet', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(359, 'Disaster Recovery', 'How often should a bank test its disaster recovery plan?', 'Never', 'At least annually or bi-annually, and after major changes', 'Every 5 years', 'Only when a disaster occurs', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(360, 'Disaster Recovery', 'What is the primary goal of disaster recovery?', 'To save money', 'To restore critical business functions within acceptable RTO and RPO', 'To replace all hardware', 'To fire employees', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(361, 'Bank Specific', 'What does \"PCI DSS\" stand for in banking IT?', 'Personal Computer Internet Data Security Standard', 'Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard — security rules for handling cardholder data', 'Program Control Interface Data System', 'Private Customer Information Storage', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(362, 'Bank Specific', 'Why is audit logging critical in a bank\'s IT systems?', 'To slow down performance', 'To provide a traceable record of who did what and when, for security and compliance', 'To fill storage', 'To confuse auditors', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(363, 'Bank Specific', 'What is the role of IT in a bank\'s business continuity?', 'Minor role', 'Critical — IT ensures systems remain available or recover quickly to prevent financial loss and reputational damage', 'No role', 'Only security', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(364, 'Bank Specific', 'A bank employee leaves the company. What IT actions must be taken?', 'Nothing', 'Disable/delete accounts, retrieve assets, revoke access, and follow offboarding procedures', 'Change their password', 'Give their computer to another employee', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(365, 'Bank Specific', 'What is \"segregation of duties\" in IT?', 'Separating offices', 'Ensuring no single person has control over all parts of a critical process to prevent fraud', 'Dividing work hours', 'Separating networks', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(366, 'Bank Specific', 'Why do banks require \"non-repudiation\" in digital transactions?', 'To make transactions slower', 'To ensure a transaction cannot be denied by either party using digital signatures and logs', 'To increase fees', 'To confuse customers', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(367, 'Bank Specific', 'What is the purpose of a \"firewall\" specifically in a bank\'s network?', 'To increase internet speed', 'To create a barrier between trusted internal network and untrusted external networks', 'To store data', 'To manage printers', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(368, 'Bank Specific', 'What is \"two-person control\" in banking IT operations?', 'Two people sharing one computer', 'Requiring two authorized individuals to perform sensitive actions (e.g., system changes)', 'Two monitors', 'Two passwords', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(369, 'Bank Specific', 'Why should bank IT staff never use production credentials in a test environment?', 'It is easier', 'Test environments may have weaker security; using production credentials risks credential theft', 'Production credentials are longer', 'Test environments are faster', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(370, 'Bank Specific', 'What is the purpose of a \"change advisory board\" (CAB) in a bank?', 'To advise on stock prices', 'To review and approve significant IT changes before implementation', 'To manage employee vacations', 'To test software', 1, 'hard', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(371, 'Bank Specific', 'What does \"end-of-life\" (EOL) mean for software or hardware?', 'The product is new', 'The vendor will no longer provide updates, patches, or support — security risk', 'The product is on sale', 'The product is free', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(372, 'Bank Specific', 'Why must banks keep an accurate hardware inventory?', 'For decoration', 'For audits, insurance, asset tracking, and to know what is connected to the network', 'To sell computers', 'To confuse IT staff', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(373, 'Bank Specific', 'What is the first thing a technician should do when a bank server room smoke alarm triggers?', 'Ignore it', 'Evacuate, follow emergency procedures, and call emergency services if needed', 'Restart all servers', 'Check the smoke detector battery', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(374, 'Bank Specific', 'What is the purpose of a \"clean desk policy\" in a bank?', 'To make desks look nice', 'To prevent sensitive information from being left visible and reduce data breach risk', 'To save space', 'To make cleaning easier', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(375, 'Bank Specific', 'Why should bank employees not write down passwords?', 'It is inconvenient', 'Written passwords can be seen or stolen, violating security policy', 'Passwords are too long', 'It is illegal', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(376, 'Bank Specific', 'What is a \"phishing simulation\" in a bank?', 'A fishing event', 'A controlled test where fake phishing emails are sent to employees to assess security awareness', 'A type of antivirus', 'A network test', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35');
