(401, 'Troubleshooting', 'A user reports that their computer restarts randomly without warning. What hardware component is MOST suspect?', 'Power supply unit (PSU) or overheating CPU', 'RAM', 'Hard drive', 'Monitor', 0, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(402, 'Troubleshooting', 'A computer takes a very long time to boot. After the OS loads, performance is normal. What is the MOST likely cause?', 'Failing RAM', 'Hard drive failing or too many startup programs', 'CPU overheating', 'Monitor cable loose', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(403, 'Troubleshooting', 'A user reports intermittent network connectivity. The technician replaces the cable but the issue persists. What is the NEXT logical step?', 'Replace the network card', 'Check the switch port and try a different port', 'Reinstall Windows', 'Replace the router', 1, 'medium', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
(404, 'Troubleshooting', 'A laptop works fine on battery but shuts down immediately when unplugged from AC power. What is the issue?', 'Faulty AC adapter', 'Dead or faulty battery', 'Motherboard failure', 'Overheating', 1, 'easy', '2026-05-23 17:18:35'),
